The paper deals with minimization problems based on a parametric family of relative entropies, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses applications in robust estimation and constrained compression, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper involves mathematical optimization and quasiconvex minimization, which are topics in mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
